"{\n  \"text\": \"Okay, here's my idea. There's a composting place at the farmer's market. Uh people give $20 to an organization to take their five-gallon buckets of kitchen waste. And I I was thinking to myself, you know, I would take their kitchen waste for free. Uh, you'll see the barrels behind me. I know what to do with this stuff. I deliver this out to a farm in Needville twice a month. I need more of it. And if I had a place that was centralized where I'm going anyway once a week, I could put a couple barrels out, maybe. People could just dump it for free. Uh I'm pretty sure Tim and Leanne would be into the idea. We'll have to talk about, see if it's up, you know. But I I could take those blue barrels, maybe put them outside the parking lot a little bit, put a sign saying, you know, free compost dump. Have people drop off their their kitchen waste. And you know, these are people who are aren't gonna be corrupting their kitchen waste, they're conscious conscientiously collecting it and paying for its its acceptance, you know, and it's processing. So these are generally people who aren't going to be giving you polluted kitchen waste full of plastic labels and all that stuff. And so it'd be great. Um, I'd love to take it. I'd love to fill if I could do four or five of these every week just from that, and I'm gonna be there anyway. I just come loop around after it's all done and collect the barrels. Wow, that'd be a great deal for me. So I'm gonna uh talk to Tim and Leanne and see if they're down. Uh I don't want to, you know, compromise the other business, uh, but I'm kind of willing to do it for free, so we'll see what they say. And what I really would like to do is to set up some other community gardeners who compost the way I do. And if you'll see behind me, I have three compost piles working. Each one of those is one of those 55-gallon drums, plus a bunch of wood chips or leaves, uh, some of my kit uh my hay from my kitchen uh chicken coop that's full of manure, uh, my own kitchen scraps, and I could deliver one of these barrels to local neighborhood gardens where they would take it, make their own good quality compost for their own garden, and then maybe I could sell some of their stuff at the farmer's market as well. They'd all be under the umbrella of living soil foods and stuff like that. I'd love to do that. And then I wouldn't have to drive the compost all the way up to Needville. I could just drop it off in the neighborhood, pick it up, drop it off, do it all on Saturday afternoon after the market. Uh man, I'm just dreaming, but we'll see. Anyway, thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Okay, here's my idea.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 2.72,\n      \"duration\": 2.4,\n      \"confidence\": 0.985,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Okay\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.987\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.94\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" here\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.04,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 1.04,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"s\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" my\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ide\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\